The paper deals with the problem of set reconciliation, which is a fundamental problem in distributed computing and falls under the category of distributed systems (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of linear sketches and characteristic polynomials, which are topics related to data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also discusses the efficiency of the reconciliation protocol in terms of communication, which is a topic related to communication complexity (cs.CC) and social and information networks (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely categories are cs.DS, cs.IT, cs.DC, cs.SI, and cs.CC.
